==Overview==
In [[Trailblazer League]], all [[Slayer masters]] assign tasks from the same list. They award the same amount of [[slayer points|points]] (15 points except for bonus tasks), have the same monster weights, and all require level 5 [[combat level|combat]] to begin receiving tasks. The slayer masters still respect combat level requirements for assigning harder tasks. [[Krystillia]] cannot assign tasks during the league, but any Slayer targets defeated within the Wilderness will have a chance to drop a [[Larran's key]].

Check the Trailblazer guide for [[Trailblazer League/Guide/Melee|melee]], [[Trailblazer League/Guide/Magic|Magic]], and [[Trailblazer League/Guide/Ranged|Ranged]] for tips on efficiently training combat during the league. 

Unlocking an [[Trailblazer League/Areas|area]] will add six new slayer monsters to the master task list. Since everyone begins the league with {{TB|Misthalin}} and {{TB|Karamja}} unlocked, the starting task list will consist of:
* [[Cows]] (while under level 50 combat)
* [[Goblins]] (while under level 50 combat)
* [[Minotaurs]] (while under level 50 combat)
* [[Zombies]] (while under level 50 combat)
* [[abyssal demon|Abyssal demons]]
* [[Ankou]]
* [[wyvern|Fossil Island wyverns]]
* [[Hill Giants]]
* [[moss giant|Moss giants]]
* [[Spiders]]
* [[sourhog|Sourhogs]] (after completing [[A Porcine of Interest]])
* [[Fire Giants]]
* [[Greater Demons]]
* [[Harpie bug swarms]]
* [[Iron dragons]]
* [[Steel dragons]]
* [[Tzhaar]]

==Farming fast slayer points==
If you are looking to get slayer points fast for unlocks and upgrades one of the fastest ways is [[Hill Giant]] and [[Moss giant|Moss Giant]] farming.  This is made incredibly easy with [[Last Recall (Trailblazer)|Last Recall]] and [[Unnatural Selection (Trailblazer)|Unnatural Selection]].

Go to any slayer master and select either Giant as a task and then teleport to Varrock. Enter [[Edgeville Dungeon]] (made easy with a [[Brass key]]). Kill Giants for your task, then use the [[Crystal of memories]] to teleport back to the slayer master. This technique gives 200+ slayer points per hour in addition to access to the giant bosses [[Obor]] and [[Bryophyta]] who with their drops give 150 league points each.

Alternatively, a spider task can be completed on the low level spiders commonly used for splashing. These can be found in the varrock sewers and near the H.A.M. hideout, as well as in the clock tower basement, for those who have unlocked Kandarin. Large numbers of aggressive spiders are also located in the 3rd level of the Stronghold of Security.

